      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"ToyCarLighting-Lighting\">Lighting</h3><p>For the lighting phase, I used a custom HDRI captured from a real-world setup I built specifically for the turntable shoot. After filming the video, I took a 360° HDRI using my phone and processed it into a usable environment map.</p><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-local-id=\"fe60ebaa-28e4-4040-9c0a-33411f89aaba\" data-macro-id=\"98f953b0-1c8f-43c9-bb1a-9e1e2e1142f5\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/1084813359\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>A quick behind-the-scenes moment with my dad while setting up the scene.</em></p><p /><p>To better control shadow definition, I added a single spotlight in CG that matched the main shadow direction seen in the footage. This allowed me to reinforce the lighting without deviating from the physical reference.</p><p>I converted the HDR image to ACEScg inside Nuke before using it in RenderMan. This ensured proper color management across the pipeline and allowed the lighting to behave predictably in CG.</p><p>The Smoking Gnome is an excellent opportunity for users to dissect a RenderMan-centric project, designed to take advantage of interactive workflows in RenderMan XPU. Play with the project, create some interesting lighting, and have fun!</p><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"image2.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581833&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=422\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/655065134/image2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581833&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"893\" data-width=\"1605\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"655097979\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"655065134\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"95be937f-ae79-4149-8f86-553e0f1ac14e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581833&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1520&amp;height=844 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581833&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=422 1x\"></span><p>Before integrating the HDRI into the scene, I performed a tone-matching step in Nuke using the mid-gray value from the checkerboard captured in the footage. This helped align the HDRI’s overall light intensity with the real-world setup, ensuring that lighting direction and energy levels in RenderMan remained both visually and physically accurate.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"image15.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image15.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581884&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=415\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/655065134/image15.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581884&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"788\" data-width=\"1443\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"655097986\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"image15.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"655065134\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"967b56ef-345d-4ab0-aee9-f423facdb70f\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image15.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581884&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1443&amp;height=788 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/655065134/image15.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762504581884&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=415 1x\"></span><hr/>"
